<!-- -*- sgml -*- -->
<sect1 id="assert.h">
 <title>Assert</title>
 <para>Access to ZeroTao Assertions is gained by adding
  <filename class=headerfile>libzt/assert.h</filename> to your project.
 </para>
 <sect2 id="assert"><title>assert - debugging with assertions</title>
 <funcsynopsis>
  <funcprototype>
    <funcdef>void <function>assert</function></funcdef>
    <paramdef>assertion <parameter>c</parameter></paramdef>
  </funcprototype>
 </funcsynopsis>
  <sect3><title>Description</title>
   <para>Overrides the standard assert to include access to 
    ZeroTao's logging facilities.  This assert works 
    exactly like the standard facility so you should 
    be able to change refrences to <filename class=headerfile>assert.h</filename>
    to <filename class=headerfile>libzt/assert.h</filename> to get access to this version.  
    This also means that you will need to define NDEBUG 
    in order to activate assertions.</para>
   </sect3>
  </sect2>
</sect1>

